[32m+[m[32m# Motion, Transitions & Scroll (Premium Constraint)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Core principle:** Motion is **subtle, intentional, and almost invisible**. If users notice the animation, it is too much.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Transition philosophy[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Minimal transitions only**—support clarity, not attention.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Avoid flashy, bouncy, or exaggerated motion.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Allowed types[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mOnly: **fade-in**, **slight translate** (prefer Y), **opacity**, **gentle scale** (minimal).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Duration & easing[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **200ms–400ms**; smooth easing only (`ease-out` or standard cubic-bezier).[m
[32m+[m[32m- Avoid: **>500ms**, linear or sharp motion.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Page load & section entry[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sections may **fade + slight slide-up (10–20px max)**; **once**, no looping.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Do **not** animate everything—key sections only.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Hover & interaction[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Subtle** color transition; slight shadow/elevation change.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Avoid: scale beyond **~1.02**, aggressive hover.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Scroll behavior[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Smooth scrolling** site-wide; natural, responsive feel.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Scroll snap (sparingly)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**OK:** full-screen hero, horizontal carousels, image galleries.[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m**Avoid:** snap on long reading pages; anything that fights normal scroll/reading.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Performance[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Prefer **`transform`** and **`opacity`** only.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Avoid animating layout: `top`, `left`, `width`, `height` (and similar).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Consistency[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **One motion style** across the site—do not mix animation “languages.”[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Accessibility[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRespect reduced motion:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```css[m
[32m+[m[32m@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {[m
[32m+[m[32m  /* disable or greatly simplify motion */[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Do not[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Parallax, autoplay motion, continuous/looping animation, complex timelines.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Heavy animation libraries unless clearly necessary.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Implementation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Prefer **CSS transitions** or **minimal utilities**; keep JS motion minimal.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Preflight (before adding motion)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Does it improve **clarity** or only look cool?[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m2. Would a **premium hotel** ship it?[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m3. Can you **remove it** and still have good UX?[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf the honest answer to (3) is yes—**do not add it**.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Goal[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMotion feels **smooth, calm, refined, and invisible**.[m
